By Sunday Aborisade President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday, asked the Senate to speedily consider three bills before the red chamber, which are aimed at further curbing corruption in Nigeria. Buhari, in the letter read at plenary by the Senate President, Ahmad Lawan, said the proposed legislation were meant to develop structures to recover proceeds of corruption and repatriate those outside the shores of the country. The bills are, proceeds of crimes bill, whistle blower bill, and the witness protection bill. Details laterâ€¦